          },
          "notes": "Stroll the charming old-town shopping street that survived WWII. Browse local shops, try menchi-katsu, and soak in the Showa-era atmosphere. Arrive early to beat the heat."
        },
        {
          "location": {
            "searchKey": "Kayaba Coffee, Yanaka, Tokyo",
            "lat": 35.7221,
            "lon": 139.7651
          },
          "day": 1,
          "startTime": {
            "value": "10:15"
          },
          "endTime": {
            "value": "11:30"
          },
          "notes": "A beloved retro kissaten that has been serving coffee since 1938. Order the morning set (toast + egg) with a pour-over. Cash only — arrive before 11:30 to secure a seat."
        },
        {
          "location": {
            "searchKey": "Tokyo National Museum, Ueno",
            "lat": 35.7188,
            "lon": 139.7764
          },
          "day": 1,
          "startTime": {
            "value": "12:00"
          },
          "endTime": {
            "value": "14:00"
          },
          "notes": "Japan's oldest and largest museum. Head to the Honkan (Japanese Gallery) for samurai armour, ceramics, and ukiyo-e woodblock prints. Pre-book tickets online to skip queues."
        },
        {
          "location": {
            "searchKey": "Nezu Shrine, Tokyo",
            "lat": 35.7215,
            "lon": 139.7598
          },
          "day": 2,
          "startTime": {
            "value": "09:00"
          },
          "endTime": {
            "value": "10:00"
          },
          "notes": "A quiet alternative to Fushimi Inari — dozens of torii gates wind through a hillside garden. Arrive early for a serene atmosphere before tour groups arrive. Free entry."
        },
        {
          "location": {
            "searchKey": "Nezu no Taiyaki, Tokyo",
            "lat": 35.7208,
            "lon": 139.7612
          },
          "day": 2,
          "startTime": {
            "value": "10:30"
          },
          "endTime": {
            "value": "11:30"
          },
          "notes": "A charming neighbourhood café and traditional snack stop near Nezu Shrine. Try a freshly grilled taiyaki (fish-shaped cake) with matcha or a light coffee. Perfect post-shrine pit stop."
        },
        {
          "location": {
            "searchKey": "Senso-ji Temple, Asakusa, Tokyo",
            "lat": 35.7148,
            "lon": 139.7967
          },
          "day": 2,
          "startTime": {
            "value": "12:30"
          },
          "endTime": {
            "value": "14:30"
          },
          "notes": "Tokyo's oldest Buddhist temple and most iconic landmark. Walk the full Nakamise shopping arcade for souvenirs, draw an omikuji fortune slip, and explore the five-storey pagoda. Go slightly off the main path to avoid crowds."
        }
